The article is a proclamation issued by President Donald J. Trump on September 17, 2020, in honor of Constitution Day and Citizenship Day. The proclamation highlights the significance of the United States Constitution as the foundation of the country's government and the protection of individual liberties. It emphasizes the division of power among branches of government and the role of the judiciary in safeguarding the Constitution. The proclamation also condemns the destruction of monuments and the attacks on American heroes by radical groups, pledging to protect the Constitution and uphold the country's freedoms. The President reaffirms the commitment to preserving the constitutional system and honoring those who have defended it. The proclamation designates September 17 as Constitution Day and Citizenship Day and September 17 to September 23 as Constitution Week.